casebody.data:
State of Connecticut v. George Guedes (6686)

Düpont, C. J., Spallone and Foti, Js.

Argued June 22 — decision released June 29, 1989 William Holden, public defender, for the appellant (defendant). Richard F. Jacobson, assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were Donald A. Browne, state’s attorney, and Henry Lyons, assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). Per Curiam.

There is no error.
